<subSubSection id="ABD3656F1B4BFFF9FF34FD93FE179361" box="[151,464,581,607]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="E37636E41B4BFFF9FF34FD93FE179361" blockId="47.[151,464,581,607]" box="[151,464,581,607]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading id="B83E81881B4BFFF9FF34FD93FE179361" bold="true" box="[151,464,581,607]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="4">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FF34FD93FE179361" bold="true" box="[151,464,581,607]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName id="24C94D671B4BFFF9FF34FD93FEB99361" baseAuthorityName="Marsham" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[151,382,581,607]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circulatus">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FF34FD93FEB99361" bold="true" box="[151,382,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mecinus circulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ABD3656F1B4BFFF9FF34FD5BFC26920A" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E37636E41B4BFFF9FF34FD5BFCD593F9" blockId="47.[151,1436,652,820]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FF34FD5BFECE939A" box="[151,265,653,676]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body elongate, subcylindrical, elytral integument reddish and black to completely black, protibiae with apical part of ventral surface distinctly directed outward.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E37636E41B4BFFF9FF64FD02FC26920A" blockId="47.[151,1436,652,820]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FF64FD02FDF193D2" box="[199,566,724,748]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks and comparative notes</emphasis>
. Within this species group, 
<taxonomicName id="24C94D671B4BFFF9FCD8FD03FBD693D2" baseAuthorityName="Marsham" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[891,1041,724,748]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circulatus">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FCD8FD03FBD693D2" box="[891,1041,724,748]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. circulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="24C94D671B4BFFF9FBEFFD03FB1193D2" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1907" box="[1100,1238,724,748]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FBEFFD03FB1193D2" box="[1100,1238,724,748]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. suturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are undoubtfully sister species due to the shape of the spermatheca as are the pair 
<taxonomicName id="24C94D671B4BFFF9FCC1FD2FFC23922E" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1795" box="[866,996,761,784]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyraster">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FCC1FD2FFC23922E" box="[866,996,761,784]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. pyraster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="24C94D671B4BFFF9FBBAFD2FFB7A922E" authorityName="Caldara &amp; Fogato" authorityYear="2013" box="[1049,1213,760,784]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baridioides">
<emphasis id="D1BDEAF61B4BFFF9FBBAFD2FFB7A922E" box="[1049,1213,760,784]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. baridioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the shape of spermatheca and ventrite 5 of the male having a tuft of hairs at the midline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
